results.name: The unique strictly superior prime divisor of each number that has one.
comment: We define a divisor d|n to be strictly superior if d > n/d. Strictly superior divisors are counted by A056924 and listed by A341673.
example: The strictly superior divisors of 15 are {5,15}, and A064052(10) = 15, so a(10) = 5.
xref: The inferior version is (largest inferior prime divisor) is A217581.
These divisors (strictly superior prime) are counted by A341642.
a(n) is the unique prime divisor in row n of A341673, for each n in A064052.
A048098 lists numbers without a strictly superior prime divisor.
A056924 counts strictly superior (or strictly inferior) divisors.
A063538/A063539 have/lack a superior prime divisors.
A140271 selects the smallest strictly superior divisor.
A238535 adds up strictly superior divisors.
